  "doc_id": "51563",
  "text": "Roles are also important for mementos. The relations between parents and children, although sharing aspects with strong-tie relations (e.g. partners in life), are asymmetric with parents taking responsibility, providing security and care [CITATION_1] . A similar dynamic is true of memories, with children focused on the self, and parents feeling a duty to preserve mementos from their children's everyday lives [CITATION_2] . The variety of objects kept is huge: artefacts and artworks, clothes, photographs, videos. The intention is to pass on these collections, especially when adult children have children themselves [CITATION_3] .",
